{{primary|date=January 2015}}
The '''Contemporary Art Society''' is an organisation founded to encourage the awareness and appreciation of [[contemporary art]] in the [[United Kingdom]]. Using money donated by its friends and supporters, it purchases works of art which it then donates to public museums and galleries.

==Background==
Founded in 1910, the Contemporary Art Society has since then donated over 8,000 works to galleries and museums, including works by [[Francis Bacon (artist)|Francis Bacon]], [[Lucien Freud]], [[Barbara Hepworth]] and [[Henry Moore]].<ref name=CAS_01>{{cite web|title=About Us|url=http://www.contemporaryartsociety.org/about/|work=Contemporary Art Society|accessdate=5 May 2014}}</ref>

The CAS enabled the donation of the ''Musgrave Kinley Outsider Art Collection'' (formed by [[Victor Musgrave]] and [[Monika Kinley]]) of about 800 works to the [[Whitworth Art Gallery]], University of Manchester, previously on loan for ten years at the [[Irish Museum of Modern Art]] (IMMA) in Dublin.<ref name=CAS>{{cite web|title=Musgrave Kinley Outsider Art Collection|url=http://www.contemporaryartsociety.org/list-of-works/musgrave-kinley-outsider-art-collection/|work=Contemporary Art Society|accessdate=5 May 2014}}</ref>

The Contemporary Art Society received funding from [[Arts Council England]] towards its core costs; in 2014-2015 this amounted to £175,655.<ref name=AC>{{cite web|title=Contemporary Art Society|url=http://www.artscouncil.org.uk/funding/browse-regularly-funded-organisations/npo/contemporary-art-society/|work=Arts Council|accessdate=5 May 2014}}</ref>

